    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>The main goals of this proposal are i) to determine accurately (&lt; 5%) the 16O/18O isotopic ratio in CO in order to improve  the measurement of the apparent  enriched anomaly of 1.3 times the solar value, and to provide a strong constraint on the origin of the non-terrestrial Titan ratio.  A terrestrial 16O/18O ratio on Titan would favor an external oxygen source of CO from Enceladus or interplanetary dust particle, while an enriched 18O would favor an initial source of enrichment. 
ii) to take benefit of the large bandwidth of ALMA to simultaneously  measure the 12C/13C, and 14N/15N  isotopic ratios in CO and HCN.  
iii) To measure CH3CCH lines available in our tunings. The isotopic measurements will add new constraints of the atmosphere history, and this new specie will improve our knowledge of Titan's chemistry. 

In order to obtain most accurate isotopic values, we need to separate equatorial and polar region where the temperature is significantly different.  Therefore, a  low resolution map (3x3) will be needed as well as signal-to-noise ratio better than 20 on C18O line. For mapping Titan’s disk(0.8”) we ask configuration C34-3, which provides a beam of 0.4” in band 7.</prp:abstract>
